WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:03.204
JIMMY:
I'm not sure she's ready
for her first sleepover.

00:03.237 --> 00:05.339
Maybe I should cancel
my bachelor party.

00:05.373 --> 00:07.308
No, then I'll feel guilty about
having my bachelorette party,

00:07.341 --> 00:09.377
and I won't be able
to enjoy watching a...

00:09.410 --> 00:11.345
very muscular half-man,
half-tripod

00:11.379 --> 00:13.081
gyrate in my no-fly zone.

00:13.114 --> 00:15.216
Well, there is not
going to be any of that

00:15.249 --> 00:16.750
happening at my party.

00:16.784 --> 00:18.652
We're just gonna be
hanging out, playing Mad Libs,

00:18.686 --> 00:21.055
see what it's like to play beer
pong sober-- never done that.

00:21.089 --> 00:23.524
And then, after a while,
if we're still going strong,
maybe we'll check out

00:23.557 --> 00:25.159
Jay Leno's take
on the day's events.

00:25.193 --> 00:27.195
Oh, come on.
Don't make me do this alone.

00:27.228 --> 00:30.698
When we compare notes,
we should both feel shameful.

00:30.731 --> 00:34.268
No, I mean...
the last time I went wild,
I knocked up a serial killer.

00:34.302 --> 00:36.770
In fact, every time I've gotten
wild, I've made bad decisions.

00:36.804 --> 00:38.406
In high school,
I became a Goth freak

00:38.439 --> 00:39.773
and I pierced my wang-doodle.

00:39.807 --> 00:41.209
That explains
the whistling noise

00:41.242 --> 00:42.743
when we were getting frisky
the other night.

00:42.776 --> 00:43.777
You know, I thought somebody
put on the teakettle.

00:43.811 --> 00:45.413
Nope.

00:45.446 --> 00:48.482
I've got a tiny, whistling
hole in my wang-doodle.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.227
What's that?

00:59.260 --> 01:01.295
Uh, nothing. Just some...

01:01.329 --> 01:04.432
boring girl stuff I bought
for the bachelorette party.

01:04.465 --> 01:08.302
So boring you had to hide it
in the vegetable crisper?

01:08.336 --> 01:10.238
(sighs)

01:10.271 --> 01:12.140
Okay, fine.

01:12.173 --> 01:14.208
It's a bag of penises.

01:14.242 --> 01:17.245
Whose are they, and why do they
have to be kept crisp?

01:17.278 --> 01:19.547
I went to the novelty store to
pick up some things for tonight,

01:19.580 --> 01:21.549
and I couldn't
stop myself!

01:21.582 --> 01:23.717
They had penis hats,
glasses, socks.

01:23.751 --> 01:25.286
But not all of it
was dirty stuff.

01:25.319 --> 01:26.654
They also had
these salt and pepper shakers

01:26.687 --> 01:29.257
that were shaped
like little mushrooms.

01:29.290 --> 01:32.826
No. Wait.
I just realized something.

01:32.860 --> 01:36.564
Ooh, I see you got some
vagina-shaped pasta.

01:36.597 --> 01:38.766
No, those are just shells.
I stopped by Howdy's.

01:40.234 --> 01:41.635
That is not fair.

01:41.669 --> 01:43.137
You're gonna have a crazy night
with the girls,

01:43.171 --> 01:44.438
and for my first bachelor party,

01:44.472 --> 01:46.174
I don't know exactly
what's gonna happen,

01:46.207 --> 01:47.841
but I've heard
the words "mocktails"

01:47.875 --> 01:49.510
and "jigsaw puzzles,"
so I don't have a good feeling.

01:49.543 --> 01:52.246
You should be proud
that your son isn't a pervert.

01:52.280 --> 01:54.315
I mean, we might have made
some mistakes here and there,

01:54.348 --> 01:57.418
but we were obviously classy
parents who made a good example.

01:57.451 --> 01:58.519
(oven timer buzzes)
Ooh!

01:58.552 --> 02:00.288
My boner scones are ready.

02:01.389 --> 02:02.823
Whoo!

02:02.856 --> 02:04.792
* Here we go

02:04.825 --> 02:08.162
* Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

02:08.196 --> 02:10.764
Okay. That's the last word.

02:10.798 --> 02:12.433
So the story is,

02:12.466 --> 02:14.502
"I was 'bored'

02:14.535 --> 02:17.505
"in my 'bored' hat
and went to my...

02:17.538 --> 02:18.872
"'boring' room, where I saw

02:18.906 --> 02:20.341
"a 'bored'
that was eating my

02:20.374 --> 02:22.176
giant 'this sucks.'"

02:22.210 --> 02:23.211
I don't think
that even makes sense.

02:23.244 --> 02:24.212
(knocking)

02:24.245 --> 02:25.246
(groans)

02:25.279 --> 02:26.514
(mumbles)

02:26.547 --> 02:27.681
Oh, hi, Tyler.

02:27.715 --> 02:29.250
Hey, I think you got
the wrong house.

02:29.283 --> 02:30.184
We didn't order
any pizzas tonight.

02:30.218 --> 02:31.552
I'm not here
on pizza business.

02:31.585 --> 02:32.820
I'm a videographer.

02:32.853 --> 02:34.522
That's why I brought
my assistants,

02:34.555 --> 02:36.290
my son and his friend,

02:36.324 --> 02:38.392
who was unfortunate enough
to be sleeping over tonight.

02:38.426 --> 02:40.461
The pizzas
are our dinner

02:40.494 --> 02:42.196
since the gentleman
who hired us

02:42.230 --> 02:43.797
refused to provide food.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.933
It's a job, man, not a buffet.

02:47.701 --> 02:49.303
Frank, this doesn't
need to be recorded.

02:49.337 --> 02:51.239
You could say that
about every single

02:51.272 --> 02:53.341
Matthew McConaughey movie
ever made,

02:53.374 --> 02:56.710
but that didn't stop Hollywood,
and it won't stop us.

03:00.281 --> 03:02.250
You're all going down.

03:02.283 --> 03:04.218
Though I guess that is kind
of the point of the game.

03:04.252 --> 03:05.753
Bitches, you don't stand
a chance.

03:05.786 --> 03:08.222
I have low self-esteem
and I'm hungry.

03:08.256 --> 03:11.225
I haven't paid
a speeding ticket since 1962.

03:11.259 --> 03:13.327
You're about to see why.

03:13.361 --> 03:14.362
Okay. On the count of three.

03:14.395 --> 03:15.363
One,

03:15.396 --> 03:16.430
two...

03:16.464 --> 03:17.431
(doorbell rings)

03:17.465 --> 03:19.233
Stripper time!

03:20.268 --> 03:22.270
Somebody order a pizza?

03:22.303 --> 03:23.971
Sabrina, we didn't
order a...

03:27.408 --> 03:28.442
...a stripper.

03:28.476 --> 03:30.278
That's a real pizza guy.

03:30.311 --> 03:31.912
Please don't judge.

03:31.945 --> 03:33.814
I get free pizza
and I sit in a car all night.

03:37.585 --> 03:41.389
Oh! Ah. I found
the corner piece.

03:41.422 --> 03:42.956
BURT: This is
a bachelor party.

03:42.990 --> 03:44.692
I want to go in the bathroom
and find a tiger.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.394
I want to get punched
in the face by Mike Tyson.

03:46.427 --> 03:48.396
I want to wake up on the roof
of a Las Vegas hotel.

03:48.429 --> 03:51.265
Like that movie The Hangover.
Didn't see it.

03:51.299 --> 03:53.434
This is a low-key night--
we're not gonna have
that kind of party.

03:53.467 --> 03:54.802
You can turn
the cameras off.

03:54.835 --> 03:57.405
Nothing crazy
is gonna happen.

03:59.473 --> 04:00.874
(knocking)

04:00.908 --> 04:02.910
Are you open?

04:04.378 --> 04:05.713
(knocking)

04:05.746 --> 04:07.415
Anyone there?

04:07.448 --> 04:09.750
Are you open?

04:09.783 --> 04:12.052
Hello?

04:12.085 --> 04:14.988
It's an emergency.

04:15.022 --> 04:18.426
I can't eat my oatmeal
without raisins!

04:18.459 --> 04:20.461
(sobs)

04:20.494 --> 04:23.497
What the hell happened?

04:26.867 --> 04:27.935
(bleating)

04:27.968 --> 04:29.337
'Sup?

04:29.370 --> 04:31.539
(chittering)

04:38.379 --> 04:40.381
Oh, jeez.

04:43.016 --> 04:44.418
Oh, boy.

04:47.821 --> 04:50.358
Oh, God.

05:01.535 --> 05:03.604
Top of the mornin'.

05:03.637 --> 05:05.473
Last night was wild.

05:05.506 --> 05:08.409
I'm not sure who remembers what,
but don't worry,

05:08.442 --> 05:10.811
Tyler and the kids
captured the whole thing.

05:10.844 --> 05:14.047
They're editing it as we speak.

05:14.081 --> 05:16.517
'Sup, drunk white people.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.118
You can turn the cameras off.

05:18.151 --> 05:19.920
Nothing crazy
is gonna happen.

05:22.590 --> 05:24.525
It's go time.

05:24.558 --> 05:28.028
MEN (chanting):
Jimmy! Jimmy! Jimmy!
Jimmy! Jimmy!

05:28.061 --> 05:29.863
What in tarnation?

05:29.897 --> 05:33.066
(chanting):
Jimmy! Jimmy! Jimmy!
Jimmy! Jimmy!

05:33.100 --> 05:36.570
Say hello to the boys
of Omicron Delta Sigma,

05:36.604 --> 05:38.038
the hardest partying fraternity

05:38.071 --> 05:40.408
Natesville Vocational School
has to offer.

05:40.441 --> 05:41.742
(barking)

05:41.775 --> 05:43.511
FRANK:
I invited them to help

05:43.544 --> 05:45.078
give you the best night
of your life.

05:45.112 --> 05:47.147
Frat guys? Kegs of beer?

05:47.180 --> 05:49.550
And a free slice of pizza
from two generous young...

05:49.583 --> 05:50.984
Ow. I'll eat chips.

05:51.018 --> 05:52.920
But it's still gonna be
a great night!

05:52.953 --> 05:55.989
Frank, I said I didn't want
a big party!

05:56.023 --> 05:57.725
I heard your words,

05:57.758 --> 06:00.528
but as your BFF--
best friend Frank--

06:00.561 --> 06:02.496
I also heard your thoughts.

06:02.530 --> 06:03.897
Frank!

06:03.931 --> 06:05.499
Stop it! Stop it!

06:05.533 --> 06:06.700
(grunting)

06:06.734 --> 06:10.103
(men barking)
(Jimmy shouting)

06:10.137 --> 06:12.440
* It's time to get
the party started *

06:12.473 --> 06:14.775
* It don't take much
for me to Mardi Gras it *

06:14.808 --> 06:15.909
