to re-pledge.
Re-pledge?

06:20.814 --> 06:22.182
22 years ago I pledged
your fraternity

06:22.215 --> 06:24.017
when I was at Natesville State.

06:24.051 --> 06:26.620
I made it all the way to when
I had to swallow the goldfish.

06:26.654 --> 06:29.590
But I chewed.
I chewed.

06:29.623 --> 06:32.593
Gross, dude.
Animal cruelty isn't cool.

06:32.626 --> 06:34.795
But if you want the honor
of calling yourself an O-Delt,

06:34.828 --> 06:36.396
just run full-speed
into that tree.

06:41.835 --> 06:43.571
(grunts)

06:43.604 --> 06:45.573
(men groan over video)

06:45.606 --> 06:47.608
Porno! Porno! Porno!

06:47.641 --> 06:48.909
JIMMY:
Whoa! Frank,

06:48.942 --> 06:50.978
we can't watch porn
back here, all right?

06:51.011 --> 06:52.580
Neighbors can see it.

06:52.613 --> 06:53.914
Then they'll get
ideas and come over.

06:53.947 --> 06:55.583
With wine coolers.

06:55.616 --> 06:58.085
Remind me to tell
you that story.
It's not porn.

06:58.118 --> 07:00.220
Aw!
FRANK: Look,
it's no secret

07:00.253 --> 07:01.922
your fiancée
and I don't get along.

07:01.955 --> 07:03.123
So I just want
to make sure

07:03.156 --> 07:04.992
you have a clear picture

07:05.025 --> 07:08.028
of the woman
you're going to call your wife.

07:10.598 --> 07:12.065
(men groan)

07:12.099 --> 07:14.101
Deal-breaker!

07:16.537 --> 07:18.739
(high-pitched flatulence)

07:18.772 --> 07:20.073
MEN (chanting):
Girls don't fart!
Girls don't fart!

07:20.107 --> 07:21.742
FRANK:
You think that's
(chuckles)

07:21.775 --> 07:23.243
disgusting, check out

07:23.276 --> 07:25.813
what she's gonna look like
in 30 years.

07:27.214 --> 07:29.182
(men groan)

07:29.216 --> 07:31.685
FRANK: For lack of a
stronger vocabulary,

07:31.719 --> 07:33.654
she looks like human diarrhea.

07:33.687 --> 07:35.956
JIMMY:
What can I say, Frank?

07:35.989 --> 07:38.025
I'm in love.

07:40.227 --> 07:43.030
All right, looks like
he still wants to do it.

07:43.063 --> 07:44.798
On to phase two.

07:44.832 --> 07:46.767
I was hoping you would change
your mind about this

07:46.800 --> 07:48.502
stupid marriage
if we caught Sabrina

07:48.536 --> 07:49.870
cheating on you,
but unfortunately,

07:49.903 --> 07:51.705
her party was pretty lame.

07:51.739 --> 07:53.741
*

07:54.975 --> 07:57.978
Honey! He's home!

08:03.617 --> 08:04.852
(muffled shouting)

08:04.885 --> 08:07.187
Are you okay?

08:07.220 --> 08:10.591
Oh, my God, did that hurt!

08:10.624 --> 08:13.527
*

08:13.561 --> 08:15.896
Why does your stripper
look like Brian,

08:15.929 --> 08:18.666
the chubby kid I went
to high school with?

08:18.699 --> 08:20.568
Hey. Jimmy Chance.

08:20.601 --> 08:22.235
Long time.
(chuckles)

08:22.269 --> 08:23.971
Quit staring, Jimmy!

08:24.004 --> 08:25.939
You're making
this awkward!

08:27.074 --> 08:29.677
Ah. Aw, keg's dead!

08:29.710 --> 08:30.611
(all groan)

08:30.644 --> 08:33.614
Where we gonna get beer
this time of night?

08:33.647 --> 08:35.583
I have keys to a grocery store!

08:35.616 --> 08:37.685
(all cheer)

08:37.718 --> 08:40.721
MEN (chanting):
Old pledge! Old pledge!
Old pledge! Old pledge!

08:40.754 --> 08:43.891
Old pledge! Old pledge!
Old pledge!

08:46.760 --> 08:48.228
It's all for us!

08:48.261 --> 08:50.297
Take it all!

08:53.634 --> 08:55.669
Whoo!

08:57.905 --> 08:59.673
(bleating)

09:02.776 --> 09:05.579
(chuckling)

09:14.688 --> 09:16.556
(chittering)

09:17.758 --> 09:19.660
Whoo-hoo!

09:19.693 --> 09:21.261
Yeah!
(men cheer)

09:21.294 --> 09:22.596
FRANK:
Everyone was having
a good time,

09:22.630 --> 09:23.897
but I had a job to do.

09:23.931 --> 09:26.099
Pull!

09:26.133 --> 09:28.602
Since none of my plans
to stop this wedding

09:28.636 --> 09:31.605
were working,
I had to go to my last resort.

09:31.639 --> 09:33.607
Check this out.
Mmm.

09:33.641 --> 09:35.776
My sister's old
wedding dress.
(chuckles)

09:35.809 --> 09:37.277
We should have a fake wedding.

09:37.310 --> 09:38.378
It'll be hilarious.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.614
To the happy couple!

09:42.149 --> 09:44.184
(groans)

09:50.023 --> 09:52.092
(all cheering)

09:54.962 --> 09:58.999
Frank, do you take Jimmy to be
your lawfully wedded partner?

09:59.032 --> 10:01.101
I do.
(chuckles)

10:01.134 --> 10:02.803
DANCIN' DAN:
And, Jimmy,

10:02.836 --> 10:05.172
do you take Frank to be
your lawfully wedded partner?

10:05.205 --> 10:06.840
I do.

10:06.874 --> 10:08.642
I always imagined
this would happen in Vegas

10:08.676 --> 10:10.778
in a little wedding chapel
while we're being chased

10:10.811 --> 10:12.112
by this little Asian guy.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.647
You mean like
in The Hangover?

10:13.681 --> 10:16.183
Has everyone seen
this movie except me?

10:16.216 --> 10:19.753
I now pronounce you
husbands for life.

10:19.787 --> 10:20.854
Whoo!
(all cheering)

10:23.156 --> 10:25.425
MEN:
Married! Married!

10:25.458 --> 10:27.427
Married! Married! Married!

10:27.460 --> 10:29.162
FRANK:
And in case you're wondering
if it's legal,

10:29.196 --> 10:31.665
here's our marriage license.

10:31.699 --> 10:33.366
Hey, Jimmy.

10:33.400 --> 10:35.936
The egg delivery guy is here,
and I can't find Barney.

10:35.969 --> 10:37.705
Will you sign for them?
Yeah.

10:40.741 --> 10:44.377
We're gonna need a witness to
prove Jimmy signed for the eggs.

10:44.411 --> 10:45.779
Yeah.

10:45.813 --> 10:48.281
So... sorry, Sabrina.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.718
You can't marry Jimmy anymore

10:50.751 --> 10:52.753
because he's already taken.

10:54.087 --> 10:55.689
(laughs)

11:01.394 --> 11:03.864
(grunting)

11:03.897 --> 11:07.034
Open the damn door,
you little freak!

11:08.068 --> 11:11.371
Oh, the ex.

11:11.404 --> 11:12.773
This is uncomfortable.

11:13.841 --> 11:16.043
You listen to me.
Oh, my God.

11:16.076 --> 11:18.178
(sighs)

11:18.211 --> 11:19.379
I forgot.
You have this whole weird town

11:19.412 --> 11:21.348
and all those creepy dolls.

11:21.381 --> 11:23.383
They're not dolls.
They're action figures.

11:23.416 --> 11:24.985
You better fix this, Frank,

11:25.018 --> 11:27.187
because you are not
messing up my wedding!

11:27.220 --> 11:30.157
I'm sorry, but if I let you guys
get married,

11:30.190 --> 11:32.893
it'll mess up the plans
I made for Jimmy and I.

11:32.926 --> 11:36.696
I mapped out a whole
future for us. Look.

11:40.834 --> 11:44.071
First, I thought
we could learn how to surf

11:44.104 --> 11:46.907
and show off our ripped bods
to the chicks at the beach.

11:46.940 --> 11:49.076
Then, with your artistic talent

11:49.109 --> 11:51.779
and my love
of frigid temperatures,

11:51.812 --> 11:54.948
I thought we could become
professional ice sculptors.

11:54.982 --> 11:57.818
Then, in the off-season,
figured we could go to Spain

11:57.851 --> 12:00.120
and run with the bulls.

12:01.955 --> 12:03.957
Just because Jimmy and I
are getting married

12:03.991 --> 12:06.393
doesn't mean you guys can't
do all that cool stuff together.

12:06.426 --> 12:08.261
Seriously?

12:08.295 --> 12:10.363
Awesome.

12:10.397 --> 12:12.800
I've got a lot of
other ideas, too.

12:12.833 --> 12:15.268
I'll be right back.

12:15.302 --> 12:16.904
(quietly):
What are you doing?

12:16.937 --> 12:18.371
I don't want
to go surfing with Frank.

12:18.405 --> 12:21.074
I'm afraid of sharks
and jellyfish and sea lions.

12:21.108 --> 12:22.810
I don't think sea lions
are what you think they are.

12:22.843 --> 12:23.944
They're the kings
of the ocean, right?

12:23.977 --> 12:25.412
No, not really.

12:25.445 --> 12:27.915
Look, we are dealing
with a mental patient here.

12:27.948 --> 12:29.917
We just have to tell him
exactly what he wants to hear,

12:29.950 --> 12:31.218
and then he'll give you
the divorce,

12:31.251 --> 12:32.820
and then we can go get married.

12:32.853 --> 12:35.088
FRANK: We are going
to have so much fun.

12:36.089 --> 12:37.991
How familiar are you

12:38.025 --> 12:41.829
with the game I just invented
called unicycle lacrosse?

12:41.862 --> 12:44.097
Yeah.

12:44.131 --> 12:46.867
Listen, I'm at
a client's house.

12:46.900 --> 12:48.936
I can't discuss this
right now.

12:48.969 --> 12:51.872
Well, I don't think you should
wear a bow tie to the meeting.

12:52.906 --> 12:54.842
Sorry about that.

12:54.875 --> 12:56.509
Trouble with another client.

12:56.543 --> 12:58.946
Sorry I'm late.

12:58.979 --> 13:01.014
I was having trouble
with my lawyer.

13:01.048 --> 13:03.583
Wait. You're
representing him, too?

13:03.616 --> 13:07.187
Oh, I'm afraid that's
attorney-client privilege.

13:07.220 --> 13:08.822
But since
you're also my client,

13:08.856 --> 13:11.491
I think I can say yes.

13:11.524 --> 13:13.160
An unusual tactic.

13:13.193 --> 13:15.028
I want to see where this goes.

13:15.062 --> 13:16.496
But be warned, counselor.

13:16.529 --> 13:18.365
You're on a short leash.

13:18.398 --> 13:19.532
(whispering):
Law and Order.

13:19.566 --> 13:20.500
WALLY:
Okay.

13:20.533 --> 13:21.969
Before my client

13:22.002 --> 13:23.837
signs these divorce papers,

13:23.871 --> 13:26.840
he's requested that you sign
a postnuptial agreement.

13:26.874 --> 13:30.878
Which my client has full right
to refuse to sign.

13:30.911 --> 13:33.413
You'll sign, or we'll
see you in court.

13:35.515 --> 13:37.150
"I, Jimmy Chance,

13:37.184 --> 13:39.452
"promise to build birdhouses
with Frank Marolla,

