13:42.422 --> 13:44.524
"do monthly mole check.

13:44.557 --> 13:46.559
"If I should fail
to fulfill these duties,

13:46.593 --> 13:48.628
"I hereby relinquish the rights
to my van

13:48.661 --> 13:50.563
"and custody of my daughter,
what's-her-name,

13:50.597 --> 13:52.399
"who will then
be raised by Frank

13:52.432 --> 13:53.500
"and immediately renamed

13:53.533 --> 13:55.168
She-Frank."

13:55.202 --> 13:56.403
I'm not signing it.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.405
Well, why not?

13:58.438 --> 14:01.208
It's just all the things
you promised we'd do together.

14:01.241 --> 14:03.977
Because I don't want
to do any of that stuff, Frank.

14:04.011 --> 14:06.980
I just want to marry the girl
I love, and if you were

14:07.014 --> 14:08.882
a real friend,
you'd understand that.

14:08.916 --> 14:09.816
Great point, Jimmy.

14:09.849 --> 14:12.920
Frank, how could you let him
say that to you?

14:12.953 --> 14:15.088
I knew this was a mistake.

14:15.122 --> 14:17.590
Never should have agreed
to this stupid meeting.

14:21.361 --> 14:23.130
This is far from over!

14:26.233 --> 14:30.003
I think we're in
pretty good shape.
This is crazy.

14:30.037 --> 14:32.339
Right? I've got to be able
to get a divorce without him.

14:32.372 --> 14:35.275
You get him to sign it,
and it'll be quick and easy.

14:35.308 --> 14:38.178
But if not, and his lawyer
gets wind of this,

14:38.211 --> 14:40.180
which he just did,

14:40.213 --> 14:42.449
then they can really
drag this out.

14:42.482 --> 14:44.117
Which I fully intend to do.

14:44.151 --> 14:45.585
What if someone cuts Frank's
brake lines

14:45.618 --> 14:46.920
and he died
in a fiery car crash?

14:46.954 --> 14:48.255
I'm spit-balling here.

14:48.288 --> 14:49.990
If anybody's got
a better idea

14:50.023 --> 14:51.124
how to kill Frank
and get away with it,

14:51.158 --> 14:52.225
the floor is yours.

14:52.259 --> 14:53.593
Wait a minute.

14:53.626 --> 14:54.995
If he wants
to be married to Jimmy,

14:55.028 --> 14:56.463
maybe we should see

14:56.496 --> 14:58.231
if he really wants
to be married to Jimmy.

14:58.265 --> 15:00.000
That's a great idea.

15:00.033 --> 15:02.469
Jimmy should pressure him
for sex constantly.

15:02.502 --> 15:04.637
He'll enjoy it
for the first couple of months,

15:04.671 --> 15:06.573
but eventually,
it'll just turn into a chore.

15:06.606 --> 15:08.141
VIRGINIA: No,
I'm not saying they should

15:08.175 --> 15:09.642
conjugate the marriage, Burt.

15:09.676 --> 15:12.079
I just think
Frank should see

15:12.112 --> 15:14.147
what it's really like spending
all his time with Jimmy.

15:14.181 --> 15:16.049
(phone ringing)

15:16.083 --> 15:17.050
Wally Phipps.

15:17.084 --> 15:20.120
Oh. You were brilliant,

15:20.153 --> 15:22.155
and that bow tie
did look great.

15:22.189 --> 15:23.957
(laughs)

15:23.991 --> 15:27.394
Oh, those Chances don't
have a chance of winning.

15:27.427 --> 15:29.229
Yeah.

15:29.262 --> 15:32.132
I don't have a fancy pun
for "Frank,"

15:32.165 --> 15:34.001
but we're gonna destroy him.

15:34.034 --> 15:36.069
Oh, wait.

15:36.103 --> 15:37.737
I'm speaking to you frankly.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.072
(laughs)

15:39.106 --> 15:41.008
Nailed it.

15:45.178 --> 15:47.147
All right, Frank thinks

15:47.180 --> 15:48.748
spending all his time
with Jimmy would be great.

15:48.781 --> 15:51.484
But what he doesn't know is what
a pain in the ass you are.

15:51.518 --> 15:54.021
- What are you talking about?
- You've got some annoying
habits.

15:54.054 --> 15:56.189
Like when you sing
in the shower.

15:56.223 --> 15:59.359
JIMMY (off-key):
* I've been working
on the railroad *

15:59.392 --> 16:02.195
* All the livelong day

16:02.229 --> 16:05.198
* I've been working
on the railroad *

16:05.232 --> 16:07.134
* Just to pass the time...
(toilet flushing)

16:07.167 --> 16:08.368
(screaming)

16:08.401 --> 16:09.302
SABRINA:
And when you're irritated,

16:09.336 --> 16:11.471
you do a play-by-play
of your every move.

16:11.504 --> 16:14.674
Oh, great, you ate
the last of the cookies.

16:14.707 --> 16:17.277
Now I've got
to pick up the plate,

16:17.310 --> 16:20.380
walk back
to the kitchen,

16:20.413 --> 16:22.049
put the plate
in the sink.

16:22.082 --> 16:23.383
(glass breaking)

16:23.416 --> 16:25.518
Pick up the broken pieces.

16:25.552 --> 16:27.054
Ah, God!

16:27.087 --> 16:29.189
Cut my finger.

16:29.222 --> 16:31.291
Now I've got to look
for a Band-Aid.

16:31.324 --> 16:33.360
And, of course,
there are none in the drawer.

16:33.393 --> 16:35.728
But I found
some cookies.

16:35.762 --> 16:38.331
Walking back
into the living room.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.702
And I'm sitting
back down.

16:42.735 --> 16:45.305
Only to see you drank
the last of the milk.

16:45.338 --> 16:46.806
Getting up again...

16:46.839 --> 16:47.674
BURT:
It drives me crazy

16:47.707 --> 16:50.277
when you only drink half
of every soda.

16:52.445 --> 16:54.414
Jimmy!

16:54.447 --> 16:57.050
Without the bubbles,
my tongue gets the flavor,

16:57.084 --> 16:58.551
but my nose doesn't get
the tickle.

16:58.585 --> 17:00.353
Puts my whole face out of whack.

17:00.387 --> 17:03.356
I mean, these are all
just bad habits.

17:03.390 --> 17:06.226
I mean, look, somebody could
have just said something.

17:06.259 --> 17:07.560
That's annoying, too.

17:07.594 --> 17:09.062
How you always make everything
our fault.

17:09.096 --> 17:10.097
Totally.

17:10.130 --> 17:11.498
Oh, yeah.

17:11.531 --> 17:14.167
All right, fine.
I'm annoying.

17:14.201 --> 17:15.702
I'll just go
and get Frank

17:15.735 --> 17:18.171
to divorce me
by being myself.

17:18.205 --> 17:19.406
And I'm headed to the door.

17:19.439 --> 17:20.740
I'm grabbing
my jacket.

17:20.773 --> 17:22.175
Ugh!

17:22.209 --> 17:24.111
Looking for
my shoes.
Ugh.

17:24.144 --> 17:25.345
Looking...

17:25.378 --> 17:27.147
The first thing I had to do

17:27.180 --> 17:28.515
was go to Frank's
and make him believe

17:28.548 --> 17:30.250
I was really moving in.

17:30.283 --> 17:31.684
Jimmy?
(loudly):
Okay.

17:31.718 --> 17:35.155
Fine. You know what?! It's over!

17:35.188 --> 17:38.091
Whoa. What happened there?

17:38.125 --> 17:40.427
What can I say, Frank?
Bitches.

17:40.460 --> 17:42.695
Does your offer still stand
to live here?

17:42.729 --> 17:44.264
Are you kidding?

17:44.297 --> 17:46.233
Our monogrammed towels
got here this morning.

17:46.266 --> 17:50.237
Of course it still stands.
Make yourself at home, hubby.

17:50.270 --> 17:52.772
JIMMY:
First, I tried annoying him
in the bathroom.

17:52.805 --> 17:55.808
JIMMY (off-key):
* Someone's in the kitchen,
I know *

17:55.842 --> 17:58.411
* Someone's in the kitchen
with Dinah *

17:58.445 --> 18:00.813
* Strummin' the old banjo

18:00.847 --> 18:03.216
FRANK:
* Fee, fie,
fiddly-i-ay *

18:03.250 --> 18:06.119
* Fee, fie,
fiddly-i-o *

18:06.153 --> 18:08.421
* Fee, fie, fiddly-i-ay

18:08.455 --> 18:10.790
* Strummin' on the old banjo.

18:12.659 --> 18:14.594
JIMMY:
Then I tried annoying him
in the kitchen.

18:14.627 --> 18:18.131
Awesome. I always said the
problem with soda is that

18:18.165 --> 18:21.168
it's too bubbly, and there's
too much of it in each can.

18:21.201 --> 18:24.271
JIMMY:
Some things I didn't even
get a chance to try.

18:24.304 --> 18:25.805
What are you doing in there?

18:25.838 --> 18:27.140
JIMMY:
I'm looking
for a glass.

18:27.174 --> 18:28.441
What about now?

18:28.475 --> 18:30.610
Rinsing the
glass out.

18:30.643 --> 18:32.145
And now?

18:32.179 --> 18:33.480
Still rinsing.

18:33.513 --> 18:34.647
Gonna be a couple minutes.

18:34.681 --> 18:36.849
You want some company?

18:36.883 --> 18:40.187
JIMMY:
Turns out Frank was so happy
to have someone in his life,

18:40.220 --> 18:42.222
he didn't care what I did.

18:42.255 --> 18:44.191
And that actually made being
married to him kind of fun.

18:44.224 --> 18:46.226
(knocking)
BURT:
Psst! Jimmy!

18:48.228 --> 18:50.530
It's been three days.
What's the holdup?

18:50.563 --> 18:52.299
Leave me alone.
All right, I'm working on it.

18:52.332 --> 18:54.334
Work faster. We got sick
of explaining where you were,

18:54.367 --> 18:55.835
so we told Hope
you were mad at her.

18:55.868 --> 18:57.304
The longer
this goes on,

18:57.337 --> 18:58.671
the worse that decision looks.

18:58.705 --> 19:00.707
Maybe it's time
to tell Frank to take a drive.

19:00.740 --> 19:04.677
You know, down a long road,
by a steep cliff.

19:04.711 --> 19:06.713
What? I'm just kidding.

19:06.746 --> 19:08.781
What? I didn't cut
his brake lines.

19:08.815 --> 19:11.351
FRANK:
Jimmy, your sardines are ready.

19:11.384 --> 19:12.285
I'll be right there!

19:12.319 --> 19:14.187
Busting out the big guns, huh?

19:14.221 --> 19:15.188
I forgot how you like
to eat those stinky sardines.

19:15.222 --> 19:16.623
He's gonna hate that.

19:16.656 --> 19:19.226
Yeah, he does hate it,
but you know what?

19:19.259 --> 19:21.661
He doesn't secretly judge me
for my annoying habits
like the rest of you.

19:21.694 --> 19:23.696
He loves me for who I am.

19:23.730 --> 19:25.298
There's no way
he loves you, Jimmy.

19:25.332 --> 19:26.699
You're going to wind up living

19:26.733 --> 19:28.668
in a cage in the basement,
I feel it.

19:28.701 --> 19:30.403
Frank is a wonderful person.

19:30.437 --> 19:33.273
He doesn't yell at me for
leaving my towel on the floor,

19:33.306 --> 19:34.674
or complain
that I'm a horrible singer.

19:34.707 --> 19:38.245
No. He harmonizes and brings me
on-key.

19:38.278 --> 19:40.213
And if that isn't a metaphor,
I don't know what is.

19:40.247 --> 19:42.215
I'm serious. I don't know
what a metaphor is.

19:42.249 --> 19:44.251
Frank wouldn't judge me
for that.

19:44.284 --> 19:46.219
(sighs)

19:46.253 --> 19:48.288
Jimmy,

19:48.321 --> 19:51.324
I just wanted to say
that these last few days

19:51.358 --> 19:54.294
have been better
than I could have ever imagined.

19:54.327 --> 19:56.329
(sighs)

19:56.363 --> 19:58.331
I've never really had
a relationship before,

19:58.365 --> 20:01.701
and every moment with you
has been a revelation.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.670
I know exactly
how you feel.

20:03.703 --> 20:06.239
I've never felt so
accepted for who I am.

20:06.273 --> 20:08.408
Me, neither.
Mmm.

20:08.441 --> 20:11.010
(sighs)
But here's the thing.

20:11.043 --> 20:14.013
I think I might rather
try it with a girl.
A girl?

20:14.046 --> 20:16.583
Yeah, you know,
for the sex part.

20:16.616 --> 20:20.620
So, you're breaking up
with me? Just like that?

20:20.653 --> 20:23.290
But there's so much stuff
that I wanted us to do together.

20:23.323 --> 20:24.791
Well, we can still
be friends, Jimmy.

20:24.824 --> 20:26.626
It's not like
we'll never see each other.

20:26.659 --> 20:28.561
We'll always have Howdy's.

20:29.962 --> 20:31.564
Let me drive you home.

20:31.598 --> 20:34.367
Whoa! Frank, no!
Um, let's walk.

20:34.401 --> 20:37.304
I mean, it's beautiful out.

20:37.337 --> 20:39.539
Sabrina cut my brakes,
didn't she?

20:39.572 --> 20:40.573
Yeah, probably.

20:42.409 --> 20:45.445
That's a damn fine woman
you got there, Jimmy.

20:45.478 --> 20:47.480
Damn fine.

20:47.514 --> 20:49.316
JIMMY:
So, the next day,

20:49.349 --> 20:51.584
Frank and I called Wally
and got a divorce.

20:51.618 --> 20:53.653
But not before
I added a post-nup

20:53.686 --> 20:55.755
to make sure
we'd always stay friends.

20:57.524 --> 21:00.993
I now pronounce you
ex-husband and ex-wife.

21:01.027 --> 21:03.496
You may now kiss
your fiancée.

21:06.399 --> 21:09.001
When I finally
find the one,

21:09.035 --> 21:11.438
I hope you'll at least
consider swapping.

21:15.342 --> 21:17.344
Adios, amigos!
